# Use `uv` for Python and Package Management

This project uses `uv` as the default Python package manager and execution tool. Always prefer `uv` over standard `pip` or `python` commands.

## Running Python Scripts

Use `uv run` to execute Python scripts to ensure they run in the correct environment.

```bash
# ❌ BAD
python script.py

# ✅ GOOD
uv run script.py
uv run python -u script.py
```

## Managing Packages

Use `uv` commands to manage dependencies instead of `pip`.

```bash
# ❌ BAD
pip install pandas
pip uninstall pandas
pip freeze > requirements.txt

# ✅ GOOD
uv add pandas
uv remove pandas
uv sync
```

## Creating Environments

Rely on `uv venv` for creating virtual environments.

```bash
# ❌ BAD
python -m venv .venv

# ✅ GOOD
uv venv
```
